	<string>Leyne uses your location to show nearby bus stops and accurate arrival times.</string>
	<!-- Leyne only ever requests when-in-use at runtime. The "always"
	     purpose string is here purely to silence App Store warning 90683:
	     some SDK in the binary (geolocator / AdMob) references the
	     CLLocationManager always-authorization API even though we never
	     call it. Apple requires the string to be present whenever the
	     symbol is referenced, regardless of runtime behaviour. -->
	<key>NSLocationAlwaysAndWhenInUseUsageDescription</key>
	<string>Leyne uses your location to show nearby bus stops and accurate arrival times.</string>
